  "text": "Previous studies have identified some splicing factors for CD44 isoform expression, such as ESRP1, hnRNPM, Tra2-β1, and KHDRBS3 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . ESRP1 regulates the expression of variant exons [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . In contrast, hnRNPM inhibits ORIGINAL RESEARCH SALL4 -KHDRBS3 network enhances stemness by modulating CD44 splicing in basal-like breast cancer the inclusion of the variant exons in CD44 mRNA [CITATION_8] . Tra2-β1 increases the expression of exons 8 and 9 [CITATION_9] . KHDRBS3 (KH RNA Binding Domain Containing, Signal Transduction Associated 3) has been identified as a regulator for CD44 exon 9 [CITATION_10] . However, the regulation of CD44 alternative splicing has not been fully understood in basal-like breast cancer.",
